{
  "title": "Refactoring REST APIs using FastAPI with Python 3.12+",
  "summary": "This guide demonstrates how to modernize existing REST APIs by leveraging FastAPI, a powerful and user-friendly framework for building web applications in Python 3.12+.",

  "key_points": [
    "FastAPI supports automatic documentation generation, type checking, and efficient request/response handling",
    "It provides a simpler syntax than Flask or Django for defining routes, handling dependencies, and validating requests",
    "Python 3.12+ features like async/await allow FastAPI to handle multiple concurrent requests with ease",
    "FastAPI can easily integrate with popular databases (SQLAlchemy), authentication libraries (JWT, OAuth2), and middlewares for additional functionality"
  ],

  "code_examples": [
